Sony’s New Console to Be Profitable Next Year, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   H o l g e r   E l f e s
-- 
2011-06-17T06:44:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-17/sony-s-new-console-to-be-profitable-next-year-handelsblatt-says.html
Sony Corp. (6758) , the world’s largest
maker of video-game players, expects its new Vita game console
to become profitable in the next fiscal year,  Handelsblatt 
reported today, citing Kazuo Hirai, head of the company’s
consumer electronics business.  The company will start selling tablet computers with an
Android operating system this year, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Holger Elfes in Dusseldorf at 
 helfes@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at 
 cperri@bloomberg.net . 